Geography.Bodies of Water:
* The [[Darkflow]] emerged from the [[Vast Swamp]], forming the border between Cormyr and [[Sembia]].
* The [[Immerflow]] poured from the [[Falls of Tumbling Stars]] in the northern [[Thunder Peaks]] and was joined by [[Turnwyrm Brook]] before flowing south into the [[Wyvernwater]].{{Cite interactive atlas|Sembia}}
* The [[Thunder River]] ran west from the southern Thunder Peaks into the Wyvernwater.
* The [[Sword River]] flowed from [[Arabel Springs]], eventually emptying into [[Wyvernwater]].{{Cite interactive atlas|Kings Forest}}

Geography.Territories:
* [[Galdyn's Gorge]], the cliffside lands of House [[Yellander]] along the [[Immerflow]].
* [[Northtrees March]], the lands of House [[Summerstar]] north of the [[Hullack Forest]].{{Cite web/Candlekeep Forum/Questions for Ed Greenwood (2004)/House Summerstar & Medicine}}
* [[Wyvernshores]], the holdings of House [[Belorgan]] on the southeastern shores of [[Wyvernwater]].

Notable Locations.Estates:
* [[Buckhaven Hall]], the fortified manor of House [[Buckfast]].
* [[Cantergates]], the country mansion of the [[Arcantlet]] family southeast of Hultail.{{Cite web/Candlekeep forum/Questions for Ed Greenwood (2009)/House Arcantlet}}
* [[Eveningspire]], an estate awarded to [[Laspeera Naerinth]] by the Crown.{{Cite dragon annual/2000/After the Dragon: The Kingdom of Cormyr Today|64}}
* [[Firefall Keep]], seat of House [[Summerstar]] in [[Firefall Vale]].
* [[Firehammer Keep]], a hold in the foothills of the Thunder Peaks.
* [[Gyrlondposts]], the estate of House [[Gyrlond]].{{Cite dungeon/194/Eye on the Realms: Thormil's Secret|2}}
* [[Hawkhar]], country estate of House [[Indesm]] and small village of their servants.{{Cite web/Candlekeep Forum/Questions for Ed Greenwood (2009)/Thunderstone Nobility}}
* [[Hullack Hall]], the home of the [[Drauthglas]] family in the Hullack Forest.{{Cite dragon/281/The New Adventures of Volo: Lost Treasures of Cormyr, Part 4|76}}
* [[Landuth Castle]], the small fortified estate of the [[Tammarast]] family on the edge of the [[Vast Swamp]].{{Cite dragon/276/The New Adventures of Volo: Cormyrian Contracts|77}}
* [[Mossfarms]], the estate of House [[Belorgan]] in [[Wyvernshores]].
* [[Shield House]], the fortified home of the [[Harper]] [[Naerlyn Phalphar]].
* [[Thawngard]], home of the noble [[Thawnfaer]]s.
* [[Whitewings]], the fortified mansion of the [[Yellander]] family in [[Galdyn's Gorge]].{{Cite web/Candlekeep Forum/Questions for Ed Greenwood (2009)/Thunderstone Nobility}}
